commit.message: Check source details before git details
Post-release CHANGELOG

Stable version v0.10.0

This release is dedicated to LLMs, for finally fulfilling the promise of
1960s scifi: systems you can hack using logic games and creative lies.
Update some copyright years
Remove outdated distros from testing
Fix snap build
Avoid stripping darwin.aarch64 binaries to keep code signature
Initial version of an ARM64 macOS build
Add extended-analysis directive to toggle DFA

commit.message:
Implement rcfile option

This introduces the "--rcfile" argument which allows a specific
shellcheckrc file to be passed.
If specified and the given file exists, the default locations
will not be searched and the specified file will be used.

Signed-off-by: Georg Pfuetzenreuter <mail@georg-pfuetzenreuter.net>

commit.message: Use maybe instead of fromMaybe and fmap
Remove most of the partial head and tail functions from src/ShellCheck/CFG.hs
Simplify isUnquotedFlag
Replace a few more occurrences of !!! with pattern matching
Simplify isTransparentCommand
Stop building tuples that we never look at both sides of
Implement isCondition in terms of foldr
Use a case expression instead of any and take 1
Switch then and else to remove a not
Simplify getStringFromParsec
Use a pattern guard instead of fromJust in checkLoopKeywordScope
Use getLiteralStringDef instead of rebuilding it with fromJust
Replace !!! with pattern-matching where it's easy
